---
// /about — who builds mitos and why. Honest, no fabricated team or metrics.
// Lifts the E-E-A-T signal (a real About page). Never use em or en dashes.
import Site from '../layouts/Site.astro';

const GITHUB = 'https://github.com/mitos-run/mitos';
const TITLE = 'About mitos: infrastructure for agent swarms';
const DESC =
  'mitos is managed, open-source infrastructure for AI agent swarms: fork a running Firecracker microVM into hundreds of isolated subagents. Why we build it.';
---

<Site title={TITLE} description={DESC}>
  <section class="hero container">
    <div class="hero-aura" aria-hidden="true"></div>
    <div class="hero-in reveal">
      <h1>Infrastructure for agent swarms.</h1>
      <p class="lede">
        mitos forks a running machine into a fleet of isolated microVMs, so one agent becomes a thousand.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a class="btn btn-primary btn-lg" href="/quickstart">Start with the open engine</a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost btn-lg" href={GITHUB} target="_blank" rel="noopener">View on GitHub</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container">
    <div class="prose">
    <p>
      Most sandbox platforms were built to <strong>run untrusted code safely</strong>. That problem
      is largely solved: microVMs are everywhere now. The pressure has moved to a harder one:
      running <strong>fleets of stateful agents in parallel</strong> for best-of-N attempts, RL
      rollouts, tree search, and large multi-agent evals.
    </p>
    <p>
      mitos is built for that. Instead of cold-booting or restoring a snapshot for every new
      environment, it <strong>forks a running Firecracker microVM</strong>: the live memory and
      processes of a warm machine are copied-on-write into hundreds of isolated daughters, each its
      own microVM, in about 27 ms and roughly 3 MiB apiece. One agent divides into a thousand.
    </p>
    <p>
      The managed cloud is the product: we run the bare-metal fleet, keep pools warm, and hand you
      an API. The engine underneath is <strong>open source under Apache 2.0</strong>, the same code
      we run. That is your no-lock-in guarantee, not a side project: you can read it, run it
      yourself, and leave whenever you want.
    </p>
    <h2>Numbers you can reproduce</h2>
    <p>
      Every figure on this site comes from a script in the open-source repository. If a claim is not
      backed by code you can run, it is not here.
    </p>
    <h2>Open source</h2>
    <p>
      The engine, SDKs, and benchmarks live on <a href={GITHUB} target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub</a>
      under Apache 2.0. Issues, discussions, and pull requests are welcome. If you want to reach us,
      see the <a href="/contact">contact page</a>.
    </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Site>

<style>
  .hero { padding-block: 184px 0; position: relative; }
  .hero-aura { position: absolute; top: -60px; left: 4%; width: 680px; max-width: 90vw; height: 520px; z-index: 0; pointer-events: none;
    background: radial-gradient(closest-side, color-mix(in srgb, var(--magenta) 11%, transparent), transparent 72%);
    opacity: .5; filter: blur(8px); }
  .hero-in { position: relative; z-index: 1; max-width: 720px; }
  .hero h1 { font-size: var(--text-display); line-height: 1.0; letter-spacing: -.035em; font-weight: 400; margin: 0 0 20px; }
  .lede { font-size: var(--text-lede); color: var(--ink-2); max-width: 34em; margin: 0 0 28px; line-height: 1.5; }
  .hero-actions { display: flex; gap: 12px; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .prose { max-width: 52em; padding-top: 56px; padding-bottom: 96px; }
  .prose p { color: var(--ink-2); font-size: var(--text-body); line-height: 1.7; margin: 0 0 22px; }
  .prose strong { color: var(--ink); font-weight: 500; }
  .prose a { color: var(--cyan); border-bottom: 1px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--cyan) 30%, transparent); }
  .prose a:hover { border-bottom-color: var(--cyan); }
  .prose h2 { font-size: var(--text-h3); font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: var(--track-display); margin: 40px 0 14px; }
  @media (max-width: 760px) { .hero { padding-block: 104px 0; } .hero h1 { font-size: var(--text-display-sm); line-height: 1.06; } }
</style>
